WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.040
Hi, I'm Sam Edwards.

00:00:08.040 --> 00:00:09.040
And I'm Gagandeep Singh.

00:00:09.040 --> 00:00:11.800
We are solutions engineers at Posit.

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:16.120
We work with customers every day, helping them turn their data science work into APIs,

00:00:16.120 --> 00:00:19.400
applications, and reports that can be used throughout their company.

00:00:19.400 --> 00:00:23.719
We are going to conduct a workshop at this year's Posit conference, focusing on building

00:00:23.719 --> 00:00:28.160
data science workflows in Python, and we would like to share top three reasons you should

00:00:28.160 --> 00:00:30.139
consider attending.

00:00:30.139 --> 00:00:31.139
Reason number one.

00:00:31.139 --> 00:00:34.799
PyPI has over 438,000 packages.

00:00:34.799 --> 00:00:37.439
Choosing the right tool for the right job can be challenging.

00:00:37.439 --> 00:00:39.080
Do people still use pandas?

00:00:39.080 --> 00:00:41.599
Does my API need to be async now?

00:00:41.599 --> 00:00:46.240
We'll discuss our favorite open-source Python tools and packages for developing end-to-end

00:00:46.240 --> 00:00:47.959
data science applications.

00:00:47.959 --> 00:00:49.040
Number two.

00:00:49.040 --> 00:00:52.240
Developing and deploying these Python applications is hard.

00:00:52.240 --> 00:00:55.680
How do I get my local web app to run in a production environment?

00:00:55.680 --> 00:00:58.840
How do I share my dash application with others?

00:00:58.840 --> 00:01:02.799
In this workshop, we will introduce you to Posit's professional products so that you

00:01:02.799 --> 00:01:06.199
can get hands-on experience with solving these problems.

00:01:06.199 --> 00:01:07.839
Lastly, this workshop will be fun.

00:01:07.839 --> 00:01:12.160
It will be a great place to meet with your fellow Pythonistas, whether you're a new Python

00:01:12.160 --> 00:01:16.559
user or a seasoned Python veteran, there'll be something at this workshop for everyone.

00:01:16.559 --> 00:01:18.879
We hope to see you in Chicago for the first ever Posit conference.

